     HTML :- HyperTex Markup Language
    ==================================
1)HTML Basics
    ->Buliding blocks of Html.(మూల భాగాలు = basic or fundamental parts)
    ->HTML DOCUMENT Structure
    ->Text formatting
    ->Creating Lists
    ->HyperLinks in HTML


    =>Buliding blocks of Html:-
        1.Tags(గుర్తులు / సూచికలు)
        2.Attributes(గుణాలు)
        3.Elements(భాగాలు)

        1)Tags:-Tags are like instructions for the browser and enclosed in
                angle brackets,like <tagename>
                Tags tell the browser how to display content on the web page.
                Ex:-<img>

        2)Attributes:-Attributes are extra information added to tags to give more details.
                    Ex:-<img src="photo.jpg">

        3)Elements:-Element is a complete part of a webpage made using (tags + content).
                    Ex:-<p>hello</p>
    

    =>HTML DOCUMENT Structure:-
        *<!DOCTYPE html>
        *<html>
        *<head>
        *<title>
        *<body>

    =>Text formatting:-
        *Heading (<h1>) → Used to create a title.
        *Paragraph (<p>) → Used to write text.
        *Strong (<strong>) → Makes text bold.
        *Emphasize (<em>) → Makes text italic.
        *Break (<br>) → Moves text to next line.
        *Horizontal line (<hr>) → Draws a line.


    =>Creating Lists:-
        *Ordered List (<ol>) – numbers the items:
          <ol><li>Apple</li>
          <li>Banana</li></ol>
        *Unordered List (<ul>) – uses bullets:
          <ul><li>Apple</li>
          <li>Banana</li></ul>
        *List Item (<li>) – each item in a list:
          <li>Apple</li>
        

    =>HyperLinks in HTML:-
        Hyperlink = clickable link to go to another page or website
        ex:-<a href="https://www.google.com">Visit Google</a>
           <a></a>=anchor tag.
